Q1) Explain Type casting and its types with examples?


Ans.


--Definition-Type casting is when you assign a value of one primitive data type to another type.

--Types of  casting-There are two types of primitive data types type castings. 
	1. Implicit Type Casting 
	2. Explicit Type Casting 

--Implicit/upcasting/Widening Casting (automatically) - converting a smaller type to a larger type size
 	
			byte -> short -> char -> int -> long -> float -> double

--Explicit/downcasting/Narrowing Casting (manually) - converting a larger type to a smaller size type

			double -> float -> long -> int -> char -> short -> byte
			

--Example of Implicit Type Casting-
		public class Main {
		  public static void main(String[] args) {
		    int x = 10;
		   double y = x; // Automatic casting: int to double
		
		    System.out.println(x);  //Outputs 10
		    System.out.println(y); //Outputs 10.0
		  }
		}


--Example of Explicit Type Casting-
		public class Main {
		  public static void main(String[] args) {
		    double doubleValue = 5.36d;
		    int intValue = (int) doubleValue; // Explicit casting: double to int
		
		    System.out.println(doubleValue);  //Outputs 5.36
		    System.out.println(intValue);   //Outputs 5
		  }
		}

